I think it's sad that we live in a country where everyone (no matter your race, ethnicity, sexual orientation, or socio-economic status) are techically afforded the same rights, but who do not actually have the same rights. That is, if you're an American citizen. Undoubtedly, it's discriminating against gay/lesbians to not allow them to marry. This is just another example of how influential religious beliefs can have upon a legal issue. Hell, I know there are plenty of heterosexual couples in our society that should not have been allowed to get married, particularly those who have married 3 or 4 times. However, I believe this will always be a debatable and prominent issue in our society, just like racism. Although it's wonderful that we can freely speak our mind and form our own opinion in this country, that liberty is often misused when people form ignorant opinions without having done their homework first.
